column2: Additional JESD configuration parameters for each JESD use case index.

column4: Number of reference clocks that transmit data is delayed through the JESD.
column14: Positive/Negative is a ratio of clocks with data versus clocks without data.   The positive sample is number of consecutive clocks with data between negative clocks.
column17: Positive/Negative is a ratio of clocks with data versus clocks without data.   The negative sample is number of consecutive clocks without data between positive clocks.
column28: Number of samples per frame minus 1.  (0=1 sample, 1=2 samples)   S parameter.
column29: Number of octets in a frame minus 1.  F parameter.
column34: Set to 0 for 16 bit, 1 for 24 bit.  N parameter.
column35: Set to 1 if JESD case uses 1p5Ghz input clock
